original: In the 7th century, the Croats, alongside other Slavic groups and Avars, migrated from Eastern Europe to the regions of the former Roman provinces of Pannonia, Dalmatia, and Istria, where they continue to reside today. The Croats, originating from an Iron Age nomadic culture, tended to avoid urban centers, opting instead to settle in rural areas surrounding Roman cities.
